race.comment: ERMINIA (4) resumes here and will find this more to her liking than her final three runs last campaign. Looks to have more upside than most of her rivals here and two jumpouts leading in suggest she's the one to beat. JUDGE KELLIE (11) is back from a break and will be improved on two recent trial placings. Fresh up record solid. Rates a leading prospect. HUGHIE (1) improved last time out, finishing a long neck from the winner in second at the end of 1100m at Kilmore after being in the firing line on the turn. Nicely placed to give this a mighty shake. INTIMEOFNEED (5) returned from a spell two-and-a-half weeks ago when she was in contention on the turn before being beaten 5 lengths into fourth over 1103m at Kyneton. Fitter so watch for a better performance.
